CVE-2021-42096 & CVE-2021-42097 GNU Mailman before 2.1.35 may allow remote Privilege Escalation. A certain csrf_token value is derived from the admin password, and may be useful in conducting a brute-force attack against that password.

For Debian 9 Stretch, these problems have been fixed in version 1:2.1.23-1+deb9u7.

We recommend that you upgrade your mailman packages.

Further information about Debian LTS security advisories, how to apply these updates to your system and frequently asked questions can be found at: [link moved to references]");

